Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Loki not starting

Solution: Check if port 3100 is already in use: sudo netstat -tulpn | grep 3100
Kill any conflicting process: sudo kill -9 <PID>
Issue: No logs appearing in queries

Solution: Verify Promtail is running: ps aux | grep promtail
Check Promtail can read the log file: sudo chmod 644 /tmp/app.log
Issue: Python script not running

Solution: Install Python if needed: sudo apt install -y python3
Check for errors: python3 app.py (run in foreground)
Issue: LogCLI returns empty results

Solution: Wait 30 seconds after starting Promtail for logs to be indexed
Verify time range: Use --since=10m for a wider time window
Issue: Permission denied errors

Solution: Ensure directories exist: sudo mkdir -p /tmp/loki/index /tmp/loki/chunks
Set proper permissions: sudo chmod -R 755 /tmp/loki
Cleanup (Optional)
Stop all services:

pkill -f loki
pkill -f promtail
pkill -f app.py
Remove temporary files:

rm -rf /tmp/loki /tmp/app.log /tmp/positions.yaml
